				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Sorry but I am going to have to start again... I read through a lot of these posts, and since the professionals at Verant can't speak their mind because it is just poor PR to put customers in their place, I will do a little defending of them myself... I saw where one person accused Gordon of looking out for his monthly income... Here's news for ya kid!  I daily look out for my income too!  Did you think EQ was some big humanitarian effort for the good of mankind?  OF COURSE they are looking out for money, but if you looked at is reasonably, you would know that it is in their best interest to keep the most people happy... So when they have an issue that won't significantly take away from gameplay, they try to give the players some say so on how the game can be improved... but in issues that will hurt gameplay (i.e., lowering the death penalty or giving away locations of loot or telling the consequences of being the first to enter new zones), they choose not to leave it open for discussion... <BR>
Verant has the right to make money, so if you don't feel that you are getting your $10/ month's worth of play, just sign off and play something else...<BR>
<BR>
As to lowering the death penalty, I have a suggestion for you... Stop dying... Play in groups with people who don't have to med, so they can watch out for unexpected MOBS like SG's and Spectres, pick your battles wisely and when you DO occasionaly die, SUCK IT UP and don't make the same mistake twice... Here is a quick little scenario that would be a problem if you dropped the death penalty... Why couldn't a newbie warrior go up and attack a guard near his initial bind point, whack away for 100 or 200 damage, die then immediately respawn and hit for another 100 to 200 hitpoints, and continue dying and respawning and killing MOB's that don't have time to regenerate... I mean they give you six levels to learn how to pick who you fight, and how to con effectively and such, so you really have no basis for complaining...<BR>
<BR>
Now for you guys that wants to know what is in the HOLE... JUMP IN IT!... You have been warned that you will die... How much more clear can that be?... What other game do you play where you know what to expect at every level?  That would completely remove the fun of the game...?<BR>
<BR>
And one final comment... Gordon has no reason to try and upset everyone... so why be so antagonistic every time you address a comment to him?  For instance, one comment said &quot;Gordon you are being inconsistent..&quot; like they are trying to catch him in some kind of deception... He has always tried to answer questions fairly and tactfully... So why the lack of respect?  I can only assume that there are a lot of young users playing this game... and as such, I am glad Gordon and Verant are doing the decision-making...<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Dayrisen<BR>
<BR>
Lowly Dark Elf <BR>
